  "id": "trendfollowing_hybrid_volatility_volume",
  "name": "Hybrid Volatility-Volume Trend Strategy",
  "description": "This trend-following strategy utilizes a hybrid volatility-volume impulse signal to identify potential entry points. It triggers when the Garman-Klass volatility increases significantly, coupled with a Positive Volume Index crossover, indicating a strong market trend supported by volume.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "I want to create a trend-following strategy using a hybrid volatility-volume impulse signal on a daily timeframe. Entry occurs when the Garman-Klass volatility over the past 14 days increases by at least 30% compared to its 28-day moving average, signaling a volatility surge. Simultaneously, the Positive Volume Index (PVI) must cross above its 10-day Weighted Moving Average, confirming volume-driven upward momentum. The system enters a long position at the next day\u2019s open if both conditions align.\n\nExit the long position when the 7-day Rolling Hurst Exponent drops below 0.45, indicating a loss of trending strength, or if the price closes below the 20-day Zero-Lag Exponential Moving Average. Short entries mirror this logic: Garman-Klass volatility spikes by 30%, but the Negative Volume Index (NVI) crosses above its 10-day WMA, signaling volume-backed downside momentum, and the system sells short at next open. Exits are triggered similarly by Rolling Hurst Exponent rising above 0.55 or price closing above the 20-day Zero-Lag EMA.\n\nThis strategy uniquely combines a volatility surge with directional volume index crossovers and trend persistence measured by Hurst exponent, aiming to capture high-probability directional moves validated by both price volatility and smart volume flows.",
